This project demonstrates how I deployed a web server using Apache on a Red Hat-based AWS EC2 instance, hosted a website, and made it accessible via the public IP.
Launch EC2 Instance
OS: Red Hat Linux (RHEL)
Enabled Ports in Security Group: 22 (SSH), 80 (HTTP), 443 (HTTPS)
sudo yum update -y
sudo yum install httpd -y
sudo systemctl start httpd
sudo systemctl enable httpd
